there was a html tag i studied, that lets what i type same as in website, it doesnt remove spaces
ChatGPT said:

The HTML tag you are thinking of is:

<pre>

The <pre> tag preserves all spaces, line breaks, tabs, and formatting exactly as you write it.

Example:

<pre>
Hello     world
   this    text
will stay    exactly
as typed
</pre>


On the website, it will appear exactly the same — no collapsing of spaces.

Why?

HTML normally collapses multiple spaces into one.
<pre> disables that behavior.

Optional: Using CSS instead

If you want any element to preserve spaces without using <pre>:

white-space: pre-wrap;


Example:

<div style="white-space: pre-wrap;">
    Hello     world
</div>


If you want, I can show you when to use <pre> vs white-space: pre-wrap.

